  "titleEn": "Five Verb Forms",
  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Object of Purpose Review",
      "titleArabic": "مراجعة المفعول لأجله",
      "content": [
        "The maf'ūl lahu indicates the reason or purpose behind an action. It must meet specific conditions to be used in the accusative without a preposition."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Must be a maṣdar (verbal noun)",
        "Must indicate reason/cause",
        "Must share subject with main verb",
        "If conditions not met, use لِ + genitive"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جِئْتُ طَلَبًا لِلْعِلْمِ", "english": "I came seeking knowledge" },
        { "arabic": "قُمْتُ إِجْلَالًا لَهُ", "english": "I stood out of respect for him" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Five Verb Forms (الأفعال الخمسة)",
      "titleArabic": "الأفعال الخمسة",
      "content": [
        "The 'five verbs' are present tense forms that end with نَ (nūn). They have special declension: retention of nūn indicates raf', omission indicates naṣb or jazm."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Forms: يَفْعَلَانِ, تَفْعَلَانِ, يَفْعَلُونَ, تَفْعَلُونَ, تَفْعَلِينَ",
        "Raf': nūn retained (يَكْتُبَانِ, يَكْتُبُونَ)",
        "Naṣb/Jazm: nūn dropped (لَنْ يَكْتُبَا, لَمْ يَكْتُبُوا)",
        "Nūn dropped when muḍāf"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "الطَّالِبَانِ يَدْرُسَانِ", "english": "The two students study (raf')" },
        { "arabic": "لَنْ يَدْرُسَا", "english": "They (dual) will not study (naṣb)" }
      ]
    }
  ],
